hands on a hard body : the documentary is a 1997 film directed by s. r. &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; documenting an endurance competition that took place in &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; , texas . the yearly competition pits twenty-four contestants against each other to see who can keep their hand on a pickup truck for the longest amount of time . whoever endures the longest without leaning on the truck or &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; wins the truck . five-minute breaks are issued every hour , and &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; breaks every six hours . the documentary follows the 1995 competition which lasted for &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; continuous hours . the film garnered the audience award for best documentary at the 1997 los angeles film festival . large portions of the film 's audio were included on the " something for nothing " episode of the public radio show this american life in 1997 . at the time of his death film director robert altman was developing a feature film based on the documentary . in 2013 , the film was digitally re-mastered and released for sale on-line .